## API Client

Use the centralized API client in `lib/api.ts`:

```typescript
import { api } from "@/lib/api";

// GET request
const data = await api.get("/api/tasks");

// POST request
const result = await api.post("/api/tasks", { title: "New task" });

// With auth header (automatic if token in localStorage)
```

## Authentication Flow

### Login

```typescript
const response = await api.post("/api/auth/login", {
  email,
  password,
  remember_me: false,
});

localStorage.setItem("token", response.accessToken);
```

### Protected Routes

Use middleware or client-side checks:

```typescript
// Client-side redirect
if (!localStorage.getItem("token")) {
  router.push("/auth/login");
}
```

## State Management

- Use React Server Components for data fetching when possible
- Use `useState` and `useEffect` for client-side state
- Consider React Query or SWR for server state caching

## Styling

Tailwind CSS is used throughout. Follow these patterns:

```typescript
// Button variants via className
<Button className={cn(
  "px-4 py-2 rounded",
  variant === "primary" && "bg-blue-600",
  variant === "secondary" && "bg-gray-200"
)}>
```

## Error Handling

Display user-friendly error messages:

```typescript
try {
  await api.post("/api/tasks", data);
} catch (error: any) {
  toast.error(error.response?.data?.error || "Failed to create task");
}
```

## Environment Variables

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` - API base URL (default: http://localhost:4000)
- Client-side env vars must start with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
